    <h3 id="ContentPage1_ctl00_h3Title" class="component_title textwindow_maintext">April 21, 2020 Update</h3>
    
    <span id="ContentPage1_ctl00_lblText" class="textwindow_text"><div>Dear CCPA Learning Community,<br><br>I trust that you and your families are safe and healthy. As we continue to deal with the  COVID-19 pandemic, it is necessary to make tough decisions that are in the best interest of our students and staff. One of those decisions was announced on April 20, 2020, during Governor DeWine‘s daily news conference. The Governor announced that all K-12 schools in the state will remain closed for the remainder of the 2019-20 school year amid the coronavirus outbreak. <br><br><br>This decision is extraordinary and represents a major shift from traditional practice. However, the nature of the current public health crisis requires us to take extreme measures. The health and safety of our students and staff continue to be our top priority.<br><br><br>We will continue working with our students and staff throughout this crisis. Remote learning will continue throughout the remainder of the school year. Online learning and paper-pencil options are available for students to continue learning. If you have any questions regarding instruction please don’t hesitate to contact us at 513-684-0777. For technology questions or assistance, <a href="https://www.ccpaonline.com/Technology.aspx">click here.</a><br><br><br>We pledge to you that we will continue to offer top quality instructional opportunities for our students until our orignally scheduled end date, May 21, 2020. Your child’s building principals and teachers will contact you with more information regarding finishing out the Spring Semester strong. Breakfast, lunch, and school pantry items will continue to be available on the <a href="https://www.ccpaonline.com/protected/ArticleView.aspx?iid=632UIAY&amp;dasi=3GA2">published schedule</a>.<br><br><br>Thank you for your continued support of the CINCINNATI COLLEGE PREPARATORY ACADEMY!</div>
<div> </div>
<div>Mr. Mathews, CCPA Superintendent </div></span>

